Saying that he’s wanted to do something a little more personal for some time now, director Michael Bay, known for such big-budget action films as  and , announced Tuesday the start of production on , a quirky romantic comedy about two unlikely explosions who fall in love.According to Bay, who also wrote the script for the film, the rom-com centers around a type-A helicopter blast who thinks it has it all figured out when a free-spirited diesel truck explosion unexpectedly enters its life and shakes everything up.“It’s really a nice little story because, on paper, these massive fireballs know they are wrong for each other, but they also have this undeniable connection they can’t ignore,” said Bay, adding that he’d actually been thinking about making a pared-down film about the small, everyday interactions between detonations since studying film in college.